SIMPLE: moron
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Moron
<hw>Mo"ron</hw> <pr>(m⟦omac⟧"r⟦ocr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>mw^ros</grk> foolish, stupid.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Pedagogy)</fld> <def>A mentally retarded person whose intellectual
development proceeds normally up to about the eighth year of age and is
then arrested so that there is little or no further development; an
adult having the mental development of an 8-to-12-year old. A
<ex>moron</ex> is considered capable of doing routine work under
supervision.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, a very stupid person.</def> <mark>[informal,
derogatory]</mark> ⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>mo*ron"ic</wf> <pos>adj.</pos> --
<wf>mo*ron"ic*al*ly</wf> <pos>adv.</pos> -- <wf>mo"ron*ism</wf>
<pos>n.</pos> -- <wf>mo*ron"i*ty</wf> <pos>n.</pos></wordforms></p>

<p><ent>Moron</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Moron
<hw>Mo*ron"</hw> <pr>(m⟦osl⟧*r⟦omac⟧n")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>Sp. pl.</it> <plw>Morones</plw> <pr>(#)</pr></plu>.
<ety>[Sp.]</ety> <def>An inferior olive size having a woody pulp and a
large clingstone pit, growing in the mountainous and high-valley
districts around the city of <etsep>Moron</etsep>, in Spain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Morone</ent>⟦br⟧
